<HEADLINE> Nigerians Unaccountably Miss HKSAR Handball Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 27 (Xinhua) -- A Nigerian team scheduled to
arrive here for their delayed appearance at the 1st Hong Kong
Special Administration Region (SAR) International Handball
Tournament failed to turn up even when it was time for them to
play on Saturday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
"I don't know the whereabouts of the Nigerians. We've just lost
contact with them," said Chan Tak-yau, chairman of the Hong Kong
Handball Association (HKHA) Saturday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the HKHA were informed, after numerous changes to
the travel schedule, that the Nigerians were to arrive here Friday
evening. But the Nigerians failed to turn up at the Kai Tak
airport, with HKHA officials waiting in vain for more than three
hours.
</P>
<P>
The tournament organizers had to cancel two of the three group
matches for Saturday which involved the Nigerian team.
</P>
<P>
"We'd feel it hard even to consider inviting them again in the
future," said an upset HKHA official. "They should have at least
informed us if they had any problem, say, on applying for a visa
on time," he added.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria was invited here for the first time.
</P>
<P>
China beat Macao 27-13 after leading 12-3 at half-time, in the
only other match in the Kowloon Park Indoor Games Hall here.
</P>
<P>
China won Group A with two straight wins, followed by Hong
Kong, China with one win and one loss, and Macao with two losses.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland of Group B downed Slovenia 37-23 on Friday, which
came out the only match of the group. Switzerland thus won the
group and Slovenia came second, with the other member of the group
Nigeria missing.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, China play Switzerland for tournament title, and
Hong Kong face Slovenia for the third place.
</P>
<P>
Macao, with no opponents to play in the next stage, has
actually taken the fifth place of the four-day tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
