<HEADLINE> Road Accidents Kill 16 in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Road accidents throughout
Greece had left 16 people dead and 261 injured since Wednesday as
thousands of Greeks rushed to provinces for Christmas holiday.
</P>
<P>
In the past four days a total of 180 road accidents have
occurred. Of the 261 injured, 45 are reported in serious
condition, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The country's road accidents annually kill 2,500 people and
injure 30,000. 
</P>
