<HEADLINE> Law Enforcement Urged in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Interior Minister
Abdollah Nouri today called for efforts to confront any illegal
actions and measures in the society, implying a control of the
recent politics-related disorder.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a nationwide gathering of governors general, Nouri
said the constitution underlines respect for the rights and
opinions of the people, therefore, any personal taste should not
influence the enforcement of laws.
</P>
<P>
According to reports, some political factions in quarrels about
different political views have announced and carried out their
"sentence" by themselves, leading to violent clashes among
supporters in some provinces which left people dead.
</P>
<P>
The situation has aroused great concern of the government and
President Mohammad Khatami, who promised freedom of speech for the
people during the May presidential elections campaigns.
</P>
<P>
Khatami said Friday that the only way to ensure a sound social
order is to accept laws as the basis of governing the nation.
</P>
<P>
Echoing Khatami's idea, Nouri stressed the constitutional
rights of political, social and economic freedoms as well as
respect for people's dignity and honor.
</P>
<P>
He also said that political development is among a priority for
the interior ministry.
</P>
<P>
Inspired by the founder of the Islamic Republic of Iran, the
late Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini, and in line with the guidelines
of the supreme leader Ayatollah Khamenei, the Interior Ministry
will do its utmost to serve justice in the society, Nouri
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
