<DOCNO> XIE19971228.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Prisoner Shot Dead at N.Ireland Jail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 27 (Xinhua) -- A leading pro-British
militiaman was shot dead today by Irish National Liberation Army
(INLA) inmates at Belfast's Maze prison.
</P>
<P>
The gunmen opened fire from the roof of an H-Block around 10:00
this morning, hitting top Loyalist Volunteer Force paramilitary
Bill Wright five times in the back, according to reports from
Belfast.
</P>
<P>
Three INL'a gunmen surrendered to the police after the shooting
and two guns were recovered.
</P>
<P>
Prison authorities are already looking into how guns were
brought into the jail to murder Wright.
</P>
<P>
The shooting is another serious breach of security at the jail
and intensifies pressure for a stricter regime.
</P>
<P>
The Maze is one of Northern Ireland's biggest jails with tight
security. 
</P>
