<DOCNO> XIE19971228.0018 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-27 19:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Leader Calls for Respect of Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian supreme leader
Ayatollah Ali Khamenei today urged the country's officials to
"meticulously carry out their duties with total respect for the
laws."
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with the country's governors general, Khamenei
said the establishment of a "highly promoted lawful society" is
among the noblest goals announced by the new government headed by
President Mohammad Khatami, Iran's official news agency IRNA
reported.
</P>
<P>
It was believed that the Iranian leader made the remarks in
response to recent violent actions taken by some radical political
factions against their rivals and what they dislike.
</P>
<P>
Reports said that several offices of political factions were
stormed by their rivals in recent months and some cinemas in
Isfahan and Amol were attacked by radicals in a protest to the
screening of the controversial film the Snowmen, which was
believed to be against Islamic values.
</P>
<P>
The violence has aroused great concern of the government of
Khatami, who promised freedom of expression for the people during
the May presidential elections campaigns.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei urged the government officials to combat actions which
will widen factional differences.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei said that the prestige of the governors general
emanate from the constitution, so they should not allow personal
motives and sentiments to obstruct the execution of the duties
mandated by the constitution.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, Khatami also called for law enforcement, saying a
law-oriented society will ensure social stability and progress.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the only way to ensure a sound social order is
to accept laws as the basis of governing the nation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
