trip to Liberia, was quoted by the News Agency of Nigeria as
saying that the chamber plans to exploit the abundant tea and
rubber plantations in Liberia to improve business relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
According to Anyaso, Nigerian businessmen would assist their
Liberian counterparts by teaching them through apprenticeship and
appointing them as distributing agents of Nigerian companies.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the Liberian business community is dominated by
Lebanese who are not interested in investing there, he said that
the aim of the chamber is to install Liberian businessmen in a
position to control business in their country.
</P>
<P>
He also urged Nigerians who had nothing good to offer Liberia
to desist from going there, saying that anybody who wanted to get
rich quick should not do so by tarnishing Nigeria's image.
</P>
