<HEADLINE> 568 Deaths on S. African Roads in December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Traffic death toll has
climbed to 568 in South Africa since December 1, traffic
authorities said today.
</P>
<P>
The figure was still expected to rise when most people wound
up their Christmas holidays and started returning from resorts,
South African Press Association quoted road safety "Arrive Alive"
campaign as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Eastern Cape Province recorded the most deaths at 106,
while Kwazulu-Natal, where the busy seaport Durban is located,
registered 95 deaths. Gauteng, which embraces Pretoria and
business capital Johannesburg, followed with 94 fatalities.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,200 people died in road accidents during last
year's Christmas and New Year holiday season. 
