<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkmenistan, Turkey Reach Cooperation Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Turkmenistan and Turkey
reached a package of bilateral cooperation agreements on Sunday,
the Interfax News Agency reported from Ashgabat, Turkmenistan.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed by Turkmen president Saparmurad
Niyazov and Turkish Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz after their
meeting Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
The main document, a tripartite agreement between Turkmenistan,
Turkey and Iran which was signed by their state ministers, deals
with the construction of a gas pipeline from Turkmenistan to
Europe through Iran and Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimate the Turkmen-Iranian gas pipeline will handle
up to 4 billion cubic meters of gas in the first year of
operation, and by the year 2006 its annual capacity will increase
to 8 billion cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
Iran guarantees the purchase of Turkmen natural gas during
the next 25 years.
</P>
<P>
Turkmenistan and Turkey also reached an accord on broading
customs cooperation and interaction between the ministries for
environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
On the same day the Turkish Prime Minister arrived in Baku, the
capital of Azerbaijian for talks with Azerbaijan President Heydar
Aliyev. 
</P>
</TEXT>
