<HEADLINE> China's First High-Speed Railway Profitable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 28 (Xinhua) -- The Guangzhou-Shenzhen Railway in
south China's Guangdong Province, the country's first high-speed
railway, has become the world's most profitable one this year.
</P>
<P>
The railway joining Guangzhou, the provincial capital and
Shenzhen, China's most flourishing special economic zone, has
safely transported 7.45 million passengers since it began
operation in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou-Shenzhen Railway Co., Ltd. is also China's only
enterprise listed on stock markets in Hong Kong and New York,
corporate sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
