<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Switzerland Wins Hong Kong SAR Handball Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 28 (Xinhua) -- A much superior Swiss team
defeated a Chinese team in the final to take the 1st Hong Kong
Special Administration Region (SAR) International Handball
Tournament here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland won the final 42-17 after leading 19-10 at
half-time. China took the second place of the four-day
tournament.
</P>
<P>
In an earlier play-off match, Slovenia downed hosts Hong Kong,
China 31-26 (half-time 16-9) to take the third place. The local
team was fourth.
</P>
<P>
Macao, who finished third in Group A preliminaries, took the
fifth place.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss team, with several national team players on the
line-up, quickly gained an upper hand in the final over the
Chinese team which was represented by a whole squad from the
Shanghai Sports Institute. The Europeans were faster and more
powerful in launching shots which beat the Chinese goalkeeper out
of balance.
</P>
<P>
"We were faster, stronger and more clever in tactics," said Urs
Muhlethaler, the team's coach.
</P>
<P>
"The Swiss team is much up over us in terms of strength and
speed. We just took the tournament as a chance to learn and for
the young players to get international experience," said Zhang
Guorong, coach of the Chinese team.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria, the other team of the six-team tournament, had failed
to turn up although they had informed the organizers that they
were to arrive here Friday evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
