<HEADLINE> New Tunnel Open to Traffic in Guangzhou Economic Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 28 (Xinhua) -- A 932-meter-long tunnel
today opened to traffic in the Guangzhou Economic and
Technological Development Zone, linking the zone's four parts.
</P>
<P>
The 100-million-yuan tunnel should improve the investment
environment of the 30-square-kilometer zone and accelerate its
development, which already has boosted the local economy in this
capital of south China's Guangdong Province, said Wang Deye,
director of the zone's management committee.
</P>
<P>
From January to November its industrial output accounted for
12.6 percent and the overseas fund was 13.8 percent of the city's
total.
</P>
<P>
Established in December of 1984, the zone has attracted 1.788
billion U.S. dollars in investment from 30 countries and regions,
including the United States, Japan and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 industrial enterprises have been set up in the
zone, producing a total industrial output of 71.6 billion U.S.
dollars and a total export volume of 2.825 billion U.S. dollars,
and turning over seven billion yuan in tax revenue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
