<HEADLINE> Mozambican Government Concerned Over Arrest of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, December 28 (Xinhua) -- The Mozambican government has
expressed concern over the arrest of Kenneth Kaunda, former
Zambian president, who is alleged to have connections with the
failed October 28 coup aimed to topple the incumbent Zambian
government.
</P>
<P>
According to local paper Domingo today, the position of the
Mozambican government was made public in a statement by the
Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Cooperation on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
The statement appealed to the Zambian government to provide
Kaunda, the outstanding African statesman, with appropriate
treatment, no matter what reasons it arrested him for.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican government also urged the Zambian government to
respect rule of law, adding that it will promote peace and
stability not only in Zambia but also in the Southern Africa
Development Community states.
</P>
<P>
Kaunda, an opposition leader in Zambia, was arrested last week
in Lusaka after his return from an overseas trip. 
</P>
