<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 28 (Xinhua) -- With the first leading factory
starting operations today, the Yangpu Economic Development Zone in
south China's island province of Hainan is entering a new stage
after five years of infrastructure construction.
</P>
<P>
The Jindao Rice Processing Factory, which formally went into
operation today, was jointly funded by the Hainan Food And Oil
Group Company and a company from Macao with an investment of 30
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
