<HEADLINE> Highway Expansion Commences in Chaozhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Chaozhou, hometown of many
overseas Chinese in the southeastern part of Guangdong,
started a highway reconstruction project today.
</P>
<P>
The 28-kilometer highway links the cities of Chaozhou and
Shantou, another Guangdong city. The project will extend the
highway's width from 14 meters to 40 meters and turn it into a
six-lane highway.
</P>
<P>
Shantou completed the reconstruction of its eight-kilometer
section of the highway last month.
</P>
<P>
The total investment for the Chaozhou highway expansion project
is 309 million yuan and will be undertaken by the Chaozhou-Shantou
Highway Construction Company Ltd. funded by the Chaozhou Highway
Construction Corp. and its Hong Kong partner.
</P>
<P>
The planned highway will take up 80 hectares along the original
highway. The reconstruction project is expected to be completed in
two years.  
</P>
