followed by Austrian-born New Zealander Claudia Riegler in 50.23
and Slovenia's Urska Hrovat in 50.29.
</P>
<P>
Reigning slalom world champion Deborah Compaganoni made a huge
mistake in the lower part of the slope and had to settle for the
ninth quickest time. 
