<HEADLINE> Five Killed in Car Collision in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Five people were killed
and five others seriously injured in a head-on collision on
Saturday on South Africa's No.1 highway linking Johannesburg and
Cape Town, South African Press Association reported today.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman said the collision between a Honda Ballade,
traveling from Cape Town to Johannesburg, and a Land Rover,
traveling in the opposite direction, happened near Richmond in
the Northern Cape Province, some 600 kilometers northeast of Cape
Town.
</P>
<P>
The four occupants of the Honda were killed instantly. One of
the occupants of the Land Rover, a 70-year-old woman, died of
injuries in hospital.
</P>
<P>
Five other family members of the woman, including three
youngsters, were in a serious condition in hospital.
</P>
<P>
The police are investigating the cause of the accident.
</P>
<P>
A total of 568 people have lost their lives between December 1
and 27, according to a nationwide road safety "Arrive Alive"
campaign.
</P>
<P>
Most of the accidents were caused by speeding and drivers
fatigue. Motorists have been urged to abide by speed limits and
rest at regular intervals. 
</P>
