<HEADLINE> Bomb Explosion Kills Three in South Sri Lankan City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 28 (Xinhua) -- A truck-bomb exploded in the
Southern Sri Lankan city of Galle early Sunday morning, killing
three people and damaging surrounding buildings, a well-informed
source said.
</P>
<P>
The source, who is working for the Sri Lankan government, said
that the bomb explosion took place at around 2:30 Sunday morning
in the main road of the city.
</P>
<P>
The dead have been identified as three Tamils. The truck was
driven into Galle from the Eastern city of Batticaloa, where the
rebel Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) has been fighting
with government troops for an independent state of their own.
</P>
<P>
The bomb exploded just 200 meters away from a naval base in
Galle, a city some 115 km south of the capital Colombo.
</P>
<P>
Before the explosion, there was a music show in town which
attracted more than 4,000 people, including some Navy commandos
and the families of soldiers killed in the civil war.
</P>
<P>
When the show finished at around 0:30, some high ranking naval
officers went along with a naval commander to their base, the
source said.
</P>
<P>
No one else was killed in the incident but the blast set
several nearby houses ablaze.
</P>
<P>
Police in the city are conducting investigations, the source
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
