<HEADLINE> Beijing Retains China's Football Association Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Guo'an defeated
Shanghai Shenhua 2-1 on a late goal from substitute Nan Fang to
retain the Chinese Football Association Cup here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Beijing defender Deng Lejun headed in an own goal in the fourth
minute of the final to give Shenhua a 1-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
Paraguayan striker Casiano Delualle then netted in the area in
the 38th minute to equalize for Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, who dominated the second half, mounted repeated
attacks and finally found the cracks in the Shanghai defence in
the 83rd minute.
</P>
<P>
Guo'an's another Paraguayan striker Andreas Oliuas Rubio
delivered a blast from left in the area but the shot was warded
off by the Shanghai goalkeeper.
</P>
<P>
Second-half substitute Nan Fang then surged ahead and pounced
on, sending the home fans at the sold-out Workers' Stadium into
ecstasy.
</P>
<P>
Beijing coach Jin Zhiyang said, "We made good preparations for
the match. We had more chances and more shots in the second
half. We deserved the win."
</P>
<P>
He said the unexpected fielding of Deng, originally a
midfielder, in the defender position was justifiable despite his
own goal.
</P>
<P>
"He worked well to check the Shanghai strikers," Jin said. "I
thought we would have had larger advantage if the Shanghai had
weaker defence."
</P>
<P>
Xie Chaoyang and Paraguayan Jorge Luis Campos, both from
Beijing, were given yellow cards in the heated match.
</P>
<P>
Beijing beat Jinan Taishan in last year's final to win the cup
for the first time. 
</P>
