when used for cultivation will enhance moisture retention in the
soil," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Sunday Mail reported today that Christian Care, another
non-governmental organization, has set aside 40 million Zimbabwe
Dollars (three million U.S. Dollars) this year as a drought
contingency fund, an amount which is slightly higher than that of
1992.
</P>
<P>
"Our organization is already networking with other NGOs, our
ecumenical partners, the government and our target communities in
preparing ourselves to assist and avoid the situation of the 1992
drought," acting national director of Christian Care Frank
Mandlokuwa said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Department of Water and Development in
collaboration with the Institute of Water and Sanitation
Development, under the Ministry for Rural Resources and Water
Development will embark on a project that seeks to investigate
appropriate methods for achieving effective water quality
monitoring.
</P>
<P>
The project, which is being funded by the Swedish embassy at a
cost of 2.8 billion Zimbabwe Dollars (200 million U.S. Dollars),
is to contribute to the establishment of sustainable water
quality management system in Zimbabwe. 
