consolidate the regional integration process started in 1991 at
its 13th summit held in Uruguay December 15.
</P>
<P>
He described the liberation of the services commerce in ten
years which ratified at this summit as "a highly important
advance".
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- The Brazilian government will invest 100 million
U.S. dollars to recover historical heritage works in seven cities
in the next two years.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian Culture Minister Francisco Weffort said December 24
that the plan will cost 200 million dollars, but half of which
will be granted by the InterAmerican Development Bank (IADB).
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Brazilian Industry, Commerce, and Tourism Minister
Francisco Dornelles said December 26 that foreign investment in
the first 11 months of this year reached 15.3 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the increase to the economic adjusting measures
its government adopted to alleviate the negative influences of the
international financial crisis, and to obtain confidence of the
overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
He said Brazil will receive 20 billion U.S. dollars of foreign
investment next year thanks to the investors' confidence in the
country.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- The Uruguayan agriculture and livestock gross
product will register an increase of 3.5 percent in 1997, its
Programming and Agriculture and Livestock Policy Office (OPYPA)
revealed December 23.
</P>
<P>
OPYPA said in its annual report that a higher livestock output
and an increase in the production of several agricultural
products, specially summer crops, contributed to the growth.
</P>
