<HEADLINE> Preparations Starts for Water Control Project in Guangxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Preparations has begun for
construction of a new water control project on the Xijiang River
near Baise, a city of south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region.
</P>
<P>
The project, which will involve a total investment of 7.78
billion yuan, is a major project for harnessing the Xijiang River
system in the Pearl River Valley in an all-round way.
</P>
<P>
It will be situated 22 km upstream of Baise and will have a
reservoir capable of storing 5.6 billion cu m of water. The
project will mainly be used for flood control, as well as for
power generation, navigation and irrigation.
</P>
<P>
When completed, the project will greatly improve the flood
combating capacity of the Youjiang River downstream and of Nanning
City, the regional capital, extending protection to 1.87 million
residents and 73,300 hectares of farmland. It will be able to
generate 1.69 billion kwh of electricity a year.
</P>
<P>
According to Wu Xijin, chairman of the board and general
manager of Youjiang River Water Resources Development Co. Ltd.of
Guangxi, preparations for the project will take one to two years
to complete.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of construction, which will take six years to
complete, will require construction of a dam, generator workshops,
a supporting dam, an upstream navigation course and other
facilities.
</P>
<P>
The preparatory work and first-phase construction will cost
6.57 billion yuan, some of which will be covered by World Bank
loans.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
