<HEADLINE> Chongqing Records Good Retooling Rice Harvest for 12 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing, a new
municipality of China, has reaped 71,000 tons of retooling rice
this year, a 47 percent rise over last year, and the 12th good
harvest.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing began to plant retooling rice on a large scale in
1986.
</P>
<P>
Now the city is growing a total of 1.05 million mu (700,000
hectares) of retooling rice, which comes from the stems of the
reaped rice.
</P>
<P>
Scientific methods have enabled the average output per mu (15
mu equals to one hectare) to hit 100 kilograms, while the highest
output has exceeded 250 kilograms. 
</P>
