<DOCNO> XIE19971228.0109 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poland to Check Illegal Entry of Foreigners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Poland's new law passed by the
parliament on June 25 for checking illegal entry of foreigners to
the country entered into force Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The law stipulates that "foreigners who are not welcomed by
Poland" will be expelled and concerned fees shall be paid by the
Polish citizen who invited the foreigners.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners who engage in illegal business in Poland will also
be repatriated and fees shall be paid by the person who employed
the foreigner, it added.
</P>
<P>
The expenses for repatriating a foreigner who entered Poland
illegally will be paid by the foreigner himself or covered the
Poland's state treasury, it said.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners shall not stay in Poland for more than one year
unless his or her stay is approved by the Polish government, it
noted.
</P>
<P>
The law also requires the Polish government not to issue visas
for those foreigners who have already been expelled once in two
years, sentenced to no less than three years in prison, suspected
of involving in anti-Poland activities or arms sales, or confirmed
as terrorists.
</P>
<P>
From 1990 to 1996, Polish police have detained 111,000
foreigners who entered Poland illegally. It is estimated that
there are 200,000 foreigners who are engaged in illegal business
in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Polish government hoped that the new law could help check
the illegal entry of foreigners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971228.0110 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Scores Progress in Space Seed Breeding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Yuan Longping, Chinese
scientist known as the "father of hybrid rice in China", has
recently turned to the research in space-treated seed breeding.
</P>
<P>
Yuan found in the second generation of space-treated seeds that
there is a kind of mutation which is 100 times over that in the
seeds treated under conventional radiation.
</P>
<P>
Yuan cultivated hybrid rice in 1973 and is trying to make a new
breakthrough in the breeding.
</P>
<P>
Since 1987, Chinese scientists have selected more than 300
sorts of seeds from about 50 kinds of crops and micro-organism to
send up to the space. Practice has proved that their efforts are
rewarding.
</P>
<P>
Chinese experts said that they are expecting to increase crop
output through the breeding of space-treated seeds. As one of the
three countries in the world that can retrieve satellites, China
enjoys the advantage of breeding seeds in space.
</P>
<P>
In 1988, China has sent a batch of rice seeds to the space and
following several years' efforts, a fine species of rice with
shorter stalks and longer kernel, disease-resistant and good
tillering capability was cultivated.
</P>
<P>
Now in Northeast China's Heilongjiang Province,
"space-treated pepper" was planted on more than 300 hectares.
</P>
<P>
According to experts, China has sent eight batches of crop
seeds into space. The space treatment operation has been extended
to insects and traditional Chinese herbs.
</P>
<P>
For the first time in 1996 Chinese scientists conducted space
seed breeding for the herb scutellaria baicalensis, the root of
large-flowered skullcap.
</P>
<P>
They acquired the second-generation seeds of the herbs in
Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Pharmacies and
found some favorable mutations.
</P>
<P>
Traditional Chinese herbs are natural pharmacies under the
guideline of the traditional Chinese medical theory. Chinese
researchers said that space-treated seed breading will check the
tendency of decreasing number and quantity of the herbs and
enhance the pharmaceutical efficiency of the herbs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971228.0111 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-28 </DATE_TIME>
