<DOCNO> XIE19971228.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Makes Progress in Poverty Alleviation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 28 (xinhua) -- The percentage of poor families
in Vietnam has dropped to 18.2 in 1997, down by 1.8 percent and
2.17 percent compared with 1996 and 1995 respectively, according
to an official report released Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The national poverty alleviation program is showing good
results, said the report issued by the Ministry of Labor, War
Invalids and Social Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, when the hunger eradication and poverty alleviation
program was launched, living conditions of some 1.21 million poor
families have improved, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Eleven provinces and cities have reduced the percentage of poor
families to below 10 percent. Among them, Hanoi, Ho Chi Minh city
and Ba Ria-Vung Tau Province are in the lead with less than 5
percent of poor families.
</P>
<P>
However, the report said that at present, there are still 2.6
million poor families in Vietnam, most of which on the northern
midlands and highlands and the central coast. About 90 percent of
the poor families are in the countryside.
</P>
<P>
Over the past three years, the percentage of poor families in
the cities and provinces has been slashed by 1.75 percent and that
in the countryside by 4.1 percent, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
