<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 24 Million Indians Carry B-Thalassemia Gene </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Over 9,000 thalassemic
children are born every year in India and there are 24 million
Indians who are carriers of the B-Thalassemia gene, the local
newspaper The Hindustan Times said here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that at least 5,000-10,000 thalassemic children
are on irregular blood transfusions.
</P>
<P>
The thalassemic children had to receive regular blood
transfusions every year. Due to the disorder, the body could not
make enough haemoglobin. While the child is well at birth, he
becomes anaemic within 3-18 months.
</P>
<P>
With every unit of blood transfused, 200-250 mg of iron also
goes into the body. It gets deposited in various organs leading to
darkened skin, discoloration of gums and teeth, liver fibrosis,
insulin dependent diabetes and even cardiac failure when iron gets
deposited on the heart muscles.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971228.0126 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 35 Hour Work Week on Italian Government Agenda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The government will open talks on
the prospect of bringing in a 35 hour work week in January,
Italian Labor Minister Tiziano Tren reported today as the
employers association Confindustria said the move to the shortened
week would carry a price tag of 31.470 trillion lire (18 billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Tren said discussions with the trade union confederations and
employers' representatives are listed among the government's
"things to do" next month for supporting employment.
</P>
<P>
He affirmed that any law on the reduced work week "must not be
parachuted in" but be drafted on the basis of dealings with labor
and employers. "There is a lot to be decided, the timetable, the
sectors, the conditions.
</P>
<P>
"The French project is a flexible type and could provide us
with some ideas," Treu added.
</P>
<P>
On the problem of joblessness, still running at more than 12
percent in Italy, the minister said the government intends to get
busy in January and February, beginning with an employment
conference to be convened.
</P>
<P>
He also said the government will follow through on the outcome
of the special European summit on employment in Luxemburg which
set guidelines for such interventions as bringing in the 35 hour
work week.
</P>
<P>
On this point, Confindustria said the impact would cost the
private sector 27.211 trillion lire (15.64 billion dollars).
Overall costs would rise 10 percent in industry, 7.2 percent in
the sector of salable services and 2.7 percent in the public
administration sector. enditem

