<HEADLINE> Speculatives Push Sensitive Index on BSE Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Speculatives made a further
headway pushing the sensitive index on the Bombay Stock Exchange
(BSE) up by another 92 points last week following continued
speculative activity coupled with good purchases by foreign
institutional investors.
</P>
<P>
The indices on the National Stock Exchange also surged up
strongly reflecting a smart rally on continued bull support and
buying from foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
