<HEADLINE> Crashed Silk Air Plane's Black Box Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 28 (Xinhua) -- A frogman unit of the
Indonesian Navy has found the black box of the Silk Air plane that
crashed on December 19 in South Sumatra, Indonesia, and the box
will be sent to the United States on Sunday, an investigation
official said.
</P>
<P>
Chief of the Indonesian investigation team from the
Transportation Ministry Prof. Oetarjo Diran said Saturday in
Palembang, South Sumatra that the Flight Data Recorder (FDR) would
be sent to the National Transport Safety Board in Washington.
</P>
<P>
By sending the FDR very soon, the cause of the plane crash will
be found out as soon as possible, local press on Sunday quoted
Oetarjo as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Silk Air Boeing 737-300 serving Jakarta-Singapore route
crashed at the Musi River in Makarti Village of Sungsang
subdistrict in the Musi Banyuasin regency, Palembang.
</P>
<P>
All 104 people on board were believed dead.
</P>
<P>
Transportation Minister Haryanto Dhanutirto, who observed the
location of the plane crash, said Saturday in Palembang that the
black box, which was found at around 3:15 p.m. local time, should
consist of an FDR and a Cockpit Voice Recording (CVR). But the CVR
had still been unfound.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the FDR was found on the bottom of the Musi
River, at the back side of the plane. However, he said, if the CVR
could not be discovered immediately, the investigation process
will be hampered.
</P>
<P>
"Basically, one of the recording is enough to carry out the
investigation, but sometimes we need two of them to make sure
about the result," Oetarjo said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
