<HEADLINE> Economic News Summary of Mercosur </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, December 27 (Xinhua) -- The following is an
economic news summary of the Southern Common Market (Mercosur):
</P>
<P>
Brazil Lifts Constraints to Imports From Mercosur
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Mercosur countries were relieved December 24
from the new Brazilian regulation on imports.
</P>
<P>
The measure was confirmed by Argentine Foreign Affairs
Ministry's International Economic Relations Secretary, Jorge
Campbell, who said to have received the announcement from his
Brazilian counterpart, Jose Botafogo Goncalves.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay Increases Exports to Mercosur
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Uruguayan sales to the Mercosur countries
accumulated 984 million dollars in the first nine months of this
year, 18 percent more than the exports to the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
Central Bank of Uruguay data show that this figure means 49
percent of the country's total exports and that Brazil was the
destination of 35 percent of Uruguayan sales abroad.
</P>
<P>
Brazil Tries to Hamper Mercosur-Canada Talks
</P>
<P>
BRAZIL -- The Brazilian government will consult with its
Mercosur partners whether to suspend the ongoing negotiations on
the conclusion of an agreement between the customs union and
Canada.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian inconformity was originated by the Canadian
cancellation of the purchase of 24 Embraer airplanes for 90
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian Foreign Affairs Ministry reacted with harsh
words, warning of the "negative effects on the perspectives of
more ample relations" between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Brazil to Open its Services Market to Mercosur Partners
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- The Brazilian government will start in February
talks to open services market to its Mercosur partners.
</P>
<P>
This stance was announced by Finance Ministry's International
Affairs Undersecretary Marco Marconini in recent statements to the
"O Estado de Sao Paulo" newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Paraguay's Economy Growth Behind Demographic Increase
</P>
<P>
ASUNCION -- The Paraguayan economy will grow 2.5 percent in
1997, not enough to cover its population increase, which will be
2.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Paraguayan Central Bank said that a financial crisis
started in the middle of the year, as well as the commercial
contraction it generated, plus the consuming political crisis, are
factors that postpone the economic reactivation.
</P>
<P>
Brazil Registers 4.41% Inflation in 1997
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- This year's Brazilian inflation, measured by the
consumer prices national index was 4.41 percent, the lowest annual
rate assessed by the Brazilian Geography and Statistics Institute.
</P>
</TEXT>
