Adams defended accurately and the two players agreed a draw after
48 moves.
</P>
<P>
The winner of the eliminator will challenge reigning FIDE world
champion Anatoly Karpov of Russia in a best-of-six contest which
will start in Lausanne, Switzerland on January 1.
</P>
<P>
The two grandmasters have battled their way through a field of
96 contestants to reach the final of the International Chess
Federation tournament in the Dutch city of Groningen, which began
on December 8. 
