have gone to 20 counties recently to provide technical services
for farmers on apple orchards of some 530,000 ha, as part of the
effort to promote rising industries through science and technology.
</P>
<P>
-- Fuzhou, the capital city of east China's Fujian Province is
making a new effort to reorganize the state assets. To date, 158
enterprises has been acquired and merged, involving 513 million
yuan in fixed assets and more 28,000 employees.
</P>
<P>
"China Youth Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- A market economy has changed the way men and women in urban
areas choose their jobs and work places. Big cities and large
enterprises, which used to people's first choice, are no longer as
attractive as before. Instead, more and more urbanites prefer to
work in a smaller township business in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
"Beijing Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China's capital has prepared sufficient supplies of goods
are now ready for the New Year's Day and the traditional Chinese
Spring Festival, with more than five billion yuan worth of
commodities on hand, a year-on-year increase of 20 percent,
including grain, cooking oil, meat, eggs and vegetables. 
</P>
