<HEADLINE> Six of Every 10 Peruvian Children Are Poor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Six of every 10 Peruvian children
and adolescents are poor. Four of them do not enjoy health care,
and one does not go to school, the latest issue of "Data Social" a
publication of the Instituto Apoyo de Peru said.
</P>
<P>
The main cause for not receiving health services and not being
registered in school is the lack of economic resources of their
families, it said.
</P>
<P>
6 percent of Peruvian adolescents do not study or work,
"which promotes their involvement with crime," the magazine added.
</P>
<P>
Data Social quoted National Police statistics as saying that
that more than 11,000 children and adolescents were arrested
between 1993 and 1996.
</P>
<P>
The magazine said that some significant achievements have been
made in recent years to reduce the rates of mortality and
infantile malnutrition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
