<DOCNO> XIE19971228.0165 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tornadoes Strike Central Florida </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 27 (Xinhua) -- Two tornadoes struck
central Florida today, injuring at least eight people and damaging
nearly 100 mobile homes, local media reports said.
</P>
<P>
The injuries, all at Haines City, Florida, were limited cuts
and bruises. Some of the mobile homes were overturned by the
storm.
</P>
<P>
Osceola County commissioners have declared a state of emergency
for the county because of a tornado.
</P>
<P>
Power and road crews were called to repair downed power lines
and remove broken trees. Many oranges were blown off trees and
some went through windows, hitting people inside. Cars and boats
were picked up and moved into other yards.
</P>
<P>
The storms followed three days of rainfall, and Saturday's
heavy rain on saturated ground caused flooding in low-lying areas
around the Tampa Bay area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
